cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with facility location problems that are inherently geometric and require analysis techniques of computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which are common in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also deals with the L1 k-median problem, which is related to clustering and could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
